  "prompt": "Top 10 website makers?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, here are ten popular website builders that are widely used for creating websites:\n\n1. **Wix**: Known for its drag-and-drop interface, Wix offers a variety of templates and features that make it easy for beginners to create visually appealing websites.\n\n2. **Squarespace**: This platform is popular for its elegant design templates and strong focus on aesthetics. It caters well to creatives and businesses looking for a professional online presence.\n\n3. **WordPress.com**: While WordPress.org is a self-hosted option, WordPress.com provides a more user-friendly experience for beginners who want to create a blog or simple website without much technical hassle.\n\n4. **Shopify**: Specifically designed for e-commerce, Shopify provides everything you need to set up an online store, including payment processing and inventory management tools.\n\n5. **Weebly**: A user-friendly website builder that also offers e-commerce capabilities. It features a drag-and-drop editor and integrated marketing tools.\n\n6. **Webflow**: This tool combines design flexibility with the power of coding. It's ideal for designers and developers who want greater control over their websites without sacrificing ease of use.\n\n7. **GoDaddy Website Builder**: GoDaddy offers a straightforward website builder with customizable templates. It is particularly useful for small businesses and offers integrated marketing tools.\n\n8. **Zyro**: A relatively new entry, Zyro offers easy-to-use tools for creating websites and digital marketing features, making it suitable for small businesses and personal projects.\n\n9. **Jimdo**: Jimdo uses AI to help users create websites quickly and easily. It's designed for simplicity and is particularly suitable for small businesses and personal use.\n\n10. **BigCommerce**: Similar to Shopify, BigCommerce specializes in e-commerce but provides more built-in features at higher tiers. It's suitable for larger online stores looking for advanced functionality.\n\nThese builders cater to different needs, whether you're looking to create a simple blog, a professional portfolio, or a comprehensive online store. Always consider your specific requirements, including budget, ease of use, and design flexibility, when choosing a website builder.",
